# Format After Code Changes

After creating or modifying TypeScript source files (e.g. `.ts` — not `.json`, `.md`, `.env`, or config files), run the following once, after all changes are completed, from the project root:

```bash
npm run format
```

Run only if at least one source file was modified.

This keeps the codebase lint-clean and consistently formatted.
